@page
@model EnableWebAuthNViewModel

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Register a WebAutnN Late Binding Token";
    ViewData.AddActivePage(ManageNavPages.TwoFactorAuthentication);
}

<h4>@ViewData["Title"]</h4>
<div>
    <p>The first release of this site enables U2F only for desktop computers. Bluetooth technologies will enable this for mobile devices soon.</p>
    <p>To enable U2F late binding tokens the first step needs to be followed once per computer where the token will be used:</p>
    <ol class="list">
        <li>
            <p>
                Depending on the browsers that are to be used with the token follow the direcitons for
                <a href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?Linkid=825071">Windows Phone</a>,
                <a href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?Linkid=825072">Android</a> and
                <a href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?Linkid=825073">iOS</a> or
                Google Authenticator for
                <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.google.android.apps.authenticator2&amp;hl=en">Android</a> and
                <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/google-authenticator/id388497605?mt=8">iOS</a>.
                The Microsoft Edge browser has not yet annouced a date when they will enable Web Authentication and the U2F tokens.

            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>Select a service where you plan to use the Late Binding Token, for example, there is a good list of soltuions providers <a href="https://www.yubico.com/solutions/#FIDO-U2F">here</a></p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>Scan the QR Code, which should appear below momentarily, or enter this key.</p>
            <div id="qrCode"></div>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Once you have scanned the QR code or input the key above, your two factor authentication app will provide you
                with a unique code, known as a time-based one-time password (totp). Enter the code in the confirmation box below.
            </p>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <form method="post">
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <!--label asp-for="Code" class="control-label">Verification Code</!--label>
                            <input asp-for="Code" class="form-control" autocomplete="off" />
                            <span asp-validation-for="Code" class="text-danger"></span-->
                        </div>
                        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default">Verify</button>
                        <div asp-validation-summary="ModelOnly" class="text-danger"></div>
                    </form>
                </div>
            </div>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

@section Scripts {
    <script type="text/javascript" src="../js/qrcode.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="~/js/site.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="~/js/finishRegister.js"></script>
    @await Html.PartialAsync("_ValidationScriptsPartial")
}
